revision.text:
The '''Belizean pine forests''' is an [[ecoregion]] that represents an example of [[lowland]] and [[premontane]] [[pine]] [[forest]]s in the [[Neotropics]], where the dominant tree species is [[Honduras Pine]]. The vegetation here is generally adapted to the [[xeric]], [[acidic]] and [[nutrient]]-poor conditions along the [[Belize]]an near coastal zone of the [[Caribbean]] versant.<ref>C. Michael Hogan & World Wildlife Fund. 2012</ref>

