{{ref improve|date=February 2013}}
[[File:Diplomatic missions of Nauru.png|thumb|right|450px|Diplomatic missions of Nauru]]
This is a '''list of diplomatic missions of Nauru''', not including its honorary consulates in [[Agana]], [[Auckland]], [[London]], [[Honolulu]], [[Pago Pago]] and [[New Delhi]]. [[Nauru]] is the smallest republic in the world.  It was previously quite wealthy, thanks to [[royalties]] collected from [[phosphate]] mining.  This allowed the country of 12,000 to expand its public service workforce to 1,600.

Economic mismanagement has forced the Nauruan government to cut back on its overseas presence.  With mounting debts it was forced to relinquish [[Nauru House]] in [[Melbourne]], a 52 story building owned by the Nauru government which housed its [[consulate-general]]. In a bid to stay solvent a covertly funded Nauran embassy was planned to be opened in [[Beijing]] as a transit point for defecting North Korean scientists ([[Operation Weasel]]).{{Citation needed|date=January 2009}}

